<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1162549>
    dc:description "FIGURES 29–31. Anaphes quinquearticulatus. 29, paratype female, mesosoma + metasoma, dorsal surface; 30, paratype female, mesosoma + metasoma, genitalia as seen throughbody; 31, holotype wings.Scale bars = 100 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1162549/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1162553>
    dc:description "FIGURES 36–39. Anaphes brevis, Same collection data as in Figs 32–35. (except Fig. 39—France, Yvelines, Béhoust, vi.1987, lab. culture ex. Lygus). 36, female, left antenna (outer surface); 37, female, right antenna (inner [medial] surface); 38, male, left antenna; 39, wings—arrow indicates socketed seta at apex of retinaculum.Scale bars = 100 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1162553/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

